formatted_address: 81 charcoal prawn pot, block 9 Toa Payoh Industrial Park, #01-1209 Good Luck Food Court Singapore 319061
name: 81 Charcoal Prawn Pot

reviews.text: Super tasty and very friendly owners!! Really enjoyed the food and dining experience. Everything nice. Hokkien mee ✅ Prawn pot ✅ fried rice ✅ we will come back!!

Probably the worst hokkien mee I had in my life.

Please note that I am not a regular at tagore. Came here to collect company delivery and saw this new shop decided to order one fried hokkien mee, $10, takeaway.

Upon returning home, to my surprise, no lard or pork was present in my hokkien mee. Is this a halal business model?

The noodles were not sufficiently fried, "Zero" wok hey detected.
Soup stock was mid so noodles tasted mid as well.

The middle aged cook was grumbling about his workload and being really moody throughout the cooking process of my wait.

Irregardless if he is the boss or staff, this shoddy attitude is highly undesirable.

The positive redeeming factors was 3 prawns provided were large and big, I applaud the fact they did not use Msg.

At the end of the day there are still better choices in yishun and AMK. If no improvements are made, I doubt this business would last more than one single year.

Regrettably, I feel that this hokkien mee has neither the value nor taste. Kindly look elsewhere.

Ordered the prawn hotpot, the prawns were very fresh and broth was super delicious. Fried rice and hokkien mee were surprisingly good too! Not forgetting the service from the bosses and the chef, top notch! Will definitely come back!

Hokkien Mee was surprisingly good! Fried Rice was also very good full of wok hey! Prawn pot was not bad but rmb to eat the prawns first otherwise they will overcook.

Overall a very satisfying meal for a cold day!
Wholesome food, huge delicious prawn, yummy sambal chilli, excellent service!

vicinity: 81 charcoal prawn pot, block 9 Toa Payoh Industrial Park, #01-1209 Good Luck Food Court, Singapore
